subSubSection.paragraph:
Aedeagus small, apex broad, widely rounded, lateraly pointed, subapically slightly constricted. Dorsal process with two sharp, slightly divergent tips, lateraly hook-like (
Fig. 1
).

Female (
Fig. 21
). Eyes smaller, interocular space wider, 2.22 time as wide as transverse diameter of eye. Antennae filiform, slightly thinner, shorter than in male, 0.61 times as long as body. Posterior coxae without process. Last ventrite with posterior margin slightly concave and with small semicircular incision in middle (
Fig. 5
). Pygidium transverse, with posterior margin straight, tergite VIII regularly rounded (
Fig. 4
). Sternite VIII with posterior margin nearly straight with two indistinct prominences in middle, with short pale setae cummulated along posterior margin, tignum twice longer than sternite VIII, narrowest in middle (
Fig. 9
). Vaginal sclerite semicircular with two darker patches (
Fig. 8
). Spermatheca as in 
Fig. 6
.

Differential diagnosis.
Having metallic blue or green elytra, 

C. borneensis

can be compared only with metallic forms of 

C. submetallica

. 

Coeligetes borneensis

can be distinguished as follows: vertex and scutellum usually dark (often orange in 

C. submetallica

) (cf. 
Figs 20, 21, 23
), males have a long thin spine on posterior trochanters (
Fig. 2
) (absent in males of 

C. submetallica

), apex of aedeagus is wider and the dorsal process has two long teeth apically (apex of aedeagus is narrower and the dorsal process has two short teeth apically in 

C. submetallica

) (
Figs 1
, 
10
), penultimate abdominal ventrite is not modified (distinctly incised and cavitous in 

C. submetallica

) (
Figs 3
, 
11
), female last ventrite with small incision in the middle of posterior margin (widely Vshaped in 

C. submetallica

) (
Figs 5
, 
13
), posterior margin of sternite VIII almost straight with two indistinct teeth in the middle (almost straight and with small semicircular incision in the middle in 

C. submetallica

) (
Figs 9
, 
16
), vaginal sclerite semicircular with two darker patches (more elongate with dark trifurcate pattern in 

C. submetallica

) (
Figs 8
, 
18
).
